          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">President Biden is expanding <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-10-01-2025-h2-2-ai-chip-export-restrictions" target="_blank">AI chip export restrictions</a> just before leaving office. The new rules limit sales to China and Russia while allowing trusted allies like Germany, Japan, and South Korea to freely access US chips. The US also has sought to prevent adversary nations from accessing cutting-edge technology through intermediaries in places like the Middle East and Southeast Asia. Nvidia has criticized the restrictions, saying they risk harming economic growth without reducing misuse. Nvidia’s shares fell 1% once the news was released.</p>
