          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">UK power prices soared as freezing weather pushed <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-10-01-2025-wn1-3-demand-for-heating" target="_blank">demand for heating</a>. Intraday power prices hit $2196.7 per megawatt-hour as the National Energy System Operator issued a rare market warning, giving the market more time to adjust. Gas-fired plants are filling the gap, generating 25 GW of power. France boosted its nuclear output to help stabilize the grid. According to grid data, scheduled interconnector flows from France to the UK have increased.</p>
