        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>EM currencies face weaker hedging support:</strong> Hedging costs for Asian currencies are falling, reducing <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-10-01-2025-m7-12-support-for-regional-currencies" target="_blank">support for regional currencies</a>. Last year’s spike in dollar gains had made hedging expensive, discouraging inflows. Hedging costs could ease with the US rates likely to stay elevated, offering better yields for dollar-funded investors. This could impact currencies like the baht and rupiah, especially as Asian central banks balance rate cuts with inflation risks.</p>
